JOHANNESBURG - Sixteen prisoners escaped from Johannesburg Correctional Centre, also known as Sun City, the Department of Correctional Services confirmed on Monday. READ:Â 5 men awaiting trial for murder escape on Golden Highway The spokesperson for the department, Singabakho Nxumalo said the inmates broke through a window, barricades and a wall before getting through the fence. He said the department has launched a manhunt for the inmates. Nxumalo said the department will release the prisoners' identities and what the crimes they are linked to, at a later stage. This is a developing story which will be updated as more information becomes available. eNCA